    "classification of unseen data samples or forecasting of unknown values).",
    "This AI category is referred to as \"task-oriented\" or \"feature-oriented\" models, which often achieved reasonable performance in terms of prediction accuracy when using an optimal quality dataset and substantial model complexity.",
    "The limitation, however, is that a new annotated dataset and a new model are required for every unique task, resulting in intensive and time consuming processes (Demrozi et al., 2023).",
    "The dependency of the model on the uniqueness of task for which it is trained is often so significant that, for example, a well performing model detecting brain tumours in tomography scans collected from one medical centre had a significant deterioration in performance when applied to similar types of scans collected from another centre (Garg et al., 2023).",
    "The second regime of AI models started with the introduction of deep learning (DL) in the early 2010s combined with the idea of transfer learning."
